00:00:01,038 --> 00:00:03,004
- Hello, glad to see you again.

2
00:00:03,004 --> 00:00:04,134
Thought today we'd do a picture

3
00:00:04,134 --> 00:00:06,071
that's right straight out of Alaska.

4
00:00:06,070 --> 00:00:07,690
We'll do one of Mount McKinley,

5
00:00:07,690 --> 00:00:11,083
the most almighty mountain in
the North American continent.

6
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:14,052
And we'll start off today,
and we use just a little bit

7
00:00:14,053 --> 00:00:16,443
of Prussian blue, maybe
a touch of phthalo green

8
00:00:16,443 --> 00:00:18,142
mixed with it here.

9
00:00:18,141 --> 00:00:21,859
And let's dance in some basic shapes here.

10
00:00:21,859 --> 00:00:23,789
I've already put the
Magic White on the canvas

11
00:00:23,789 --> 00:00:26,326
to save a little time.

12
00:00:26,327 --> 00:00:29,552
So we're just literally
mixing color right here

13
00:00:29,551 --> 00:00:31,801
on the canvas, just let this brush

14
00:00:31,801 --> 00:00:34,966
dance and play and have fun.

15
00:00:34,966 --> 00:00:37,368
And all we're looking for is general basic

16
00:00:37,368 --> 00:00:38,649
cloud shapes here, we're really not

17
00:00:38,649 --> 00:00:41,632
trying to put anything in.

18
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,493
Just let it happen.

19
00:00:43,493 --> 00:00:46,411
Just move the brush,
keep it moving, working,

20
00:00:46,411 --> 00:00:48,603
playing, having fun, there we go.

21
00:00:48,603 --> 00:00:50,552
Isn't that something?

22
00:00:50,552 --> 00:00:51,635
There we are.

23
00:00:52,511 --> 00:00:57,471
Put a nice little cloud shape
right there, what the heck.

24
00:00:57,470 --> 00:01:01,387
Okay, keep the brush
moving, don't let it stop.

25
00:01:04,804 --> 00:01:06,365
And sometimes brush is lazy, you have to

26
00:01:06,364 --> 00:01:08,908
really push it a little
or it'll quit on you.

27
00:01:08,908 --> 00:01:10,575
Make it keep moving.

28
00:01:11,784 --> 00:01:16,016
Okay, now we'll take
the almighty brush here,

29
00:01:16,016 --> 00:01:17,489
and we're gonna swirl this.

30
00:01:17,489 --> 00:01:21,017
We're gonna pull the color, move it,

31
00:01:21,016 --> 00:01:23,470
pull it, there we go.

32
00:01:23,471 --> 00:01:26,831
Try to avoid a pattern, we
want this to go everywhere.

33
00:01:26,831 --> 00:01:29,558
We're looking for a sky
here that has life in it,

34
00:01:29,558 --> 00:01:31,505
has movement in it, we don't want a sky

35
00:01:31,504 --> 00:01:33,705
that looks like at night
you pull the curtain down

36
00:01:33,706 --> 00:01:35,871
and everything went black on you.

37
00:01:35,871 --> 00:01:38,371
Wanna keep this moving, there.

38
00:01:40,551 --> 00:01:41,573
Already you're beginning to see

39
00:01:41,572 --> 00:01:45,563
all the little things happening up here.

40
00:01:45,563 --> 00:01:47,396
Every which direction.

41
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,150
Every way, there we go.

42
00:01:53,483 --> 00:01:55,525
Now you can blend this too
much and take it all out.

43
00:01:55,525 --> 00:01:58,980
We don't wanna take it out,
we just wanna mix it up.

44
00:01:58,980 --> 00:01:59,897
Stir it up.

45
00:02:04,251 --> 00:02:06,562
Okay, while we've got some
paint on the brush here,

46
00:02:06,563 --> 00:02:10,729
we'll add a little more
Prussian blue and phthalo green.

47
00:02:12,301 --> 00:02:15,384
And we'll put us in some water.

48
00:02:15,384 --> 00:02:17,717
We pull from the outside in.

49
00:02:19,051 --> 00:02:21,096
And leave a little area opened here,

50
00:02:21,096 --> 00:02:24,462
that will create the little sheen of light

51
00:02:24,461 --> 00:02:26,794
that plays across the water.

52
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:29,675
You can go back with white
paint and put it back in,

53
00:02:29,675 --> 00:02:32,599
but you've already covered
the canvas with Magic White,

54
00:02:32,598 --> 00:02:34,098
so why not use it?

55
00:02:35,016 --> 00:02:38,099
This is a lazy man's way of painting.

56
00:02:39,502 --> 00:02:42,915
You let the paint work,
you let the brushes work.

57
00:02:42,914 --> 00:02:46,497
Use what happens
naturally, don't fight it.

58
00:02:50,955 --> 00:02:54,203
Okay, clean the old brush off,

59
00:02:54,204 --> 00:02:57,683
and let's get out an
almighty fan brush here.

60
00:02:57,683 --> 00:03:01,036
And let's build some happy
little clouds up here.

61
00:03:01,036 --> 00:03:04,949
I'm gonna take titanium white
with the least little touch

62
00:03:04,949 --> 00:03:06,866
of permanent red in it.

63
00:03:08,413 --> 00:03:12,202
And load the brush full of
paint, just really load it up.

64
00:03:12,203 --> 00:03:14,598
Now we'll start working on
some basic cloud shapes here,

65
00:03:14,598 --> 00:03:16,924
and we'll dance in all these little areas

66
00:03:16,925 --> 00:03:19,675
and let 'em just play in the sky.

67
00:03:21,474 --> 00:03:24,641
Keep the brush moving, keep it moving.

68
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:29,715
You want areas that are
thick, areas that are thin.

69
00:03:29,715 --> 00:03:32,632
Let all these little things happen.

70
00:03:34,027 --> 00:03:35,930
And we'll take the big brush here

71
00:03:35,931 --> 00:03:39,104
and gently, gently blend this together.

72
00:03:39,104 --> 00:03:40,187
Very lightly.

73
00:03:41,628 --> 00:03:45,128
And fluff it up a little and hypnotize it.

74
00:03:46,019 --> 00:03:48,061
And right there you've
got an almighty cloud,

75
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,394
just that quick.

76
00:03:50,497 --> 00:03:53,967
But they're very easily
killed, clouds are delicate.

77
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:58,530
Don't overwork it, put
it in, leave it alone.

78
00:03:58,531 --> 00:04:00,117
Okay, and maybe we'll
have another one here.

79
00:04:00,117 --> 00:04:03,200
We'll put a, layer these clouds some.

80
00:04:05,281 --> 00:04:06,114
Okay.

81
00:04:10,114 --> 00:04:14,281
Nature is so beautiful, just
let it go, have fun with it.

82
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:21,216
Very, very easy to work these to death.

83
00:04:27,468 --> 00:04:29,841
Okay, we'll blend this in.

84
00:04:29,841 --> 00:04:31,458
And you work in layers here, you do thing

85
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:33,936
that's the farthest away first,

86
00:04:33,935 --> 00:04:37,352
have him finished, and then work forward.

87
00:04:39,451 --> 00:04:41,793
There, we'll hypnotize that one,

88
00:04:41,793 --> 00:04:44,127
blend this one a little bit.

89
00:04:47,548 --> 00:04:50,132
Okay, little bit more red here.

90
00:04:52,168 --> 00:04:53,823
There we go.

91
00:04:53,824 --> 00:04:55,638
Don't wanna set these clouds on fire now.

92
00:04:55,637 --> 00:04:59,689
All we wanna do is have a
slight warmish glow to 'em,

93
00:04:59,689 --> 00:05:02,773
like the sun's playing along the top.

94
00:05:04,021 --> 00:05:05,021
There we go.

95
00:05:07,636 --> 00:05:09,542
Guess we better not forget
this side of the sky.

96
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:13,578
We'll put a little something over here.

97
00:05:13,579 --> 00:05:17,745
Just some nice little clouds
playing around in the sky.

98
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,559
Okay, and mix these up a little bit.

99
00:05:24,559 --> 00:05:27,642
(lively piano music)

100
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:37,292
Okay, maybe a little
streaky one right here.

101
00:05:39,437 --> 00:05:40,551
Got baby clouds, too.

102
00:05:40,552 --> 00:05:41,479
If you didn't have baby clouds,

103
00:05:41,478 --> 00:05:43,895
you wouldn't have big clouds.

104
00:05:45,134 --> 00:05:49,301
There, and we can work on
this one a little touch.

105
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:58,470
Okay, there looks like a nice place.

106
00:06:00,742 --> 00:06:02,930
And we're really pushing
this paint into the canvas.

107
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:07,180
We're working that value
right into the canvas.

108
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:08,597
Just let it play.

109
00:06:09,656 --> 00:06:12,435
Don't kill all the dark areas.

110
00:06:12,435 --> 00:06:14,872
You can end up with great
big cotton balls in the sky

111
00:06:14,872 --> 00:06:16,705
if you're not careful.

112
00:06:20,098 --> 00:06:21,658
Guess that'd be considered a UFO,

113
00:06:21,658 --> 00:06:24,680
big cotton ball in the sky.

114
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,430
There, fluff that up.

115
00:06:30,766 --> 00:06:32,432
And work that paint.

116
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:36,970
And look at there, in
just a couple of minutes,

117
00:06:36,970 --> 00:06:41,137
you have a sky that has so
much action happening in it.

118
00:06:42,990 --> 00:06:44,490
There we go, okay.

119
00:06:48,951 --> 00:06:51,682
(banging)

120
00:06:51,682 --> 00:06:52,795
If you do this in your living room,

121
00:06:52,795 --> 00:06:55,338
you can redecorate your living
room in a matter of minutes,

122
00:06:55,338 --> 00:06:58,549
so be very careful, learn to control it.

123
00:06:58,548 --> 00:07:00,212
Have you a box you can
shake your brush in,

124
00:07:00,213 --> 00:07:02,299
and that way you don't have to worry about

125
00:07:02,298 --> 00:07:03,965
covering everything.

126
00:07:05,266 --> 00:07:09,222
Okay, let's take a little
bit of brown, some blue,

127
00:07:09,221 --> 00:07:13,388
a little touch of alizarin
crimson and some white.

128
00:07:15,461 --> 00:07:17,901
There we go, and don't
mix your paint dead.

129
00:07:17,901 --> 00:07:20,891
Mix it marbley and leave it alone.

130
00:07:20,891 --> 00:07:23,912
Okay, now let's do, since
we're gonna do McKinley today,

131
00:07:23,911 --> 00:07:26,440
let's do the basic shape here.

132
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:30,924
McKinley comes down like
so, has another peak

133
00:07:30,925 --> 00:07:33,752
running right off through here.

134
00:07:33,752 --> 00:07:36,836
Make that just a little more rounded.

135
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:44,006
There, and we let this side
drop right down and over.

136
00:07:46,862 --> 00:07:48,865
All you're looking for
here is the basic outline,

137
00:07:48,865 --> 00:07:51,596
the basic shape of this mountain.

138
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:55,048
You're not worried at
all what happens in here.

139
00:07:55,048 --> 00:07:59,215
Okay, take the big brush,
and we'll pull that down.

140
00:08:02,379 --> 00:08:05,147
This takes off the excess paint

141
00:08:05,148 --> 00:08:07,254
and makes the next layer stick better.

142
00:08:07,254 --> 00:08:08,521
And also when you're doing mountains,

143
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:11,497
if you can see the entire
mountain, the top of the mountain

144
00:08:11,497 --> 00:08:15,290
is always more distinct than the bottom.

145
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:17,102
At the bottom of the
mountain we have mist,

146
00:08:17,101 --> 00:08:18,798
and now we have pollution.

147
00:08:18,798 --> 00:08:21,137
We have a multitude of
things that break up

148
00:08:21,137 --> 00:08:22,637
and diffuse light.

149
00:08:26,809 --> 00:08:30,698
Okay, and we'll put some snow
on that almighty mountain.

150
00:08:30,697 --> 00:08:33,189
Pull that paint out real
flat, just pull it out

151
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:35,861
and get us a little roll of paint.

152
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:40,028
And we'll just lay this on and
let it travel right on down.

153
00:08:42,941 --> 00:08:44,850
And you want the paint to break like this,

154
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,634
to make all the little
things that happen in there,

155
00:08:47,634 --> 00:08:51,384
the little shadows, the
light and dark areas.

156
00:08:52,886 --> 00:08:55,469
Okay, and there's a little bump

157
00:08:56,756 --> 00:08:58,923
that comes out right there

158
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:02,408
and works its way down.

159
00:09:04,399 --> 00:09:07,899
And over here, let this drop just like so.

160
00:09:15,571 --> 00:09:16,571
There we go.

161
00:09:19,177 --> 00:09:21,860
Now for the shadow
color, we'll use a little

162
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:23,860
Prussian blue and white.

163
00:09:27,850 --> 00:09:30,247
And once again, don't mix it dead.

164
00:09:30,246 --> 00:09:33,079
You want it to be sort of marbley.

165
00:09:34,244 --> 00:09:38,144
Okay, now we'll start with the shadows,

166
00:09:38,144 --> 00:09:39,353
and we'll just lay these in here.

167
00:09:39,354 --> 00:09:43,104
We wanna bring these
two areas here together.

168
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:46,040
So we just sorta work it back and forth

169
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:48,386
and let it come, there you go,

170
00:09:48,385 --> 00:09:50,552
let it just come together.

171
00:09:51,892 --> 00:09:56,059
And maybe this shadow comes
right down through here.

172
00:09:58,971 --> 00:10:02,721
Every highlight needs
its own private shadow.

173
00:10:09,794 --> 00:10:12,231
Okay, we'll put a little
shadow right there.

174
00:10:12,231 --> 00:10:14,084
And see how that protrudes that up?

175
00:10:14,085 --> 00:10:16,485
Makes it just jump right out at you.

176
00:10:16,485 --> 00:10:19,581
The little ridges here and there.

177
00:10:19,581 --> 00:10:23,749
All kind of little things
happening in this mountain.

178
00:10:24,828 --> 00:10:28,516
And we need a shadow back here
behind this almighty peak.

179
00:10:28,517 --> 00:10:29,517
There it is.

180
00:10:30,698 --> 00:10:32,031
Just let him go.

181
00:10:38,082 --> 00:10:42,904
Okay, and we want a peak that
comes right up through here

182
00:10:42,904 --> 00:10:45,970
and just begins working its way back down.

183
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:49,052
(lively piano music)

184
00:10:56,457 --> 00:10:57,290
There.

185
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:04,473
It's a nice ridge coming through here.

186
00:11:04,472 --> 00:11:06,371
And we can bring these together.

187
00:11:06,371 --> 00:11:09,454
(lively piano music)

188
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:17,077
A few little shadows in here.

189
00:11:18,172 --> 00:11:19,839
Just here and there.

190
00:11:24,326 --> 00:11:25,158
Okay.

191
00:11:27,302 --> 00:11:30,235
And as we say, we want
this to be more distinct

192
00:11:30,235 --> 00:11:31,975
at the top than the bottom, so we're gonna

193
00:11:31,975 --> 00:11:35,096
diffuse the bottom of
it, and only the bottom.

194
00:11:35,096 --> 00:11:37,446
And here we're just tapping the canvas.

195
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:40,809
We're trying not to destroy, only diffuse.

196
00:11:40,808 --> 00:11:43,382
And this is where you really
depend on a firm paint.

197
00:11:43,383 --> 00:11:46,605
If you have a loose, oily, thin paint,

198
00:11:46,605 --> 00:11:48,937
you become a mud mixer here.

199
00:11:52,626 --> 00:11:55,335
So when you try this at home,

200
00:11:55,336 --> 00:11:57,485
if you find that you're
making a lot of mud,

201
00:11:57,485 --> 00:12:00,072
check your paint, it
should be very, very firm.

202
00:12:00,072 --> 00:12:02,511
Squeeze that tube, it
should stand up maybe about

203
00:12:02,511 --> 00:12:05,396
three-quarters of an inch above the tube.

204
00:12:05,397 --> 00:12:08,174
Then you have a nice firm paint.

205
00:12:08,173 --> 00:12:10,621
Okay, I'm gonna make the same
color and make it darker.

206
00:12:10,621 --> 00:12:13,788
Blue, brown, and alizarin added to it.

207
00:12:15,789 --> 00:12:17,894
'Cause I want this
mountain to be in front.

208
00:12:17,894 --> 00:12:19,889
This is a beautiful study
of how to make one mountain

209
00:12:19,889 --> 00:12:21,557
look very, very big.

210
00:12:22,618 --> 00:12:24,569
And we'll put some
little smaller mountains

211
00:12:24,568 --> 00:12:26,224
here in the foreground.

212
00:12:26,225 --> 00:12:29,307
(lively piano music)

213
00:12:33,852 --> 00:12:36,435
Okay, another little peak here.

214
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:47,611
And we'll take the big
brush and pull that out.

215
00:12:47,611 --> 00:12:50,528
Son of a gun, this comes right out.

216
00:12:52,051 --> 00:12:54,983
That's the beauty of painting wet on wet.

217
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:57,732
You can move paint on the canvas.

218
00:13:01,028 --> 00:13:04,729
And we'll put some happy little snow here.

219
00:13:04,729 --> 00:13:06,229
Just let that run.

220
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,320
There we go.

221
00:13:13,462 --> 00:13:14,295
Okay.

222
00:13:16,037 --> 00:13:18,287
Our light is still coming
from the same direction here,

223
00:13:18,287 --> 00:13:21,072
so don't let that fool you.

224
00:13:21,072 --> 00:13:24,154
(lively piano music)

225
00:13:30,937 --> 00:13:34,519
Okay, now we can work
in some shadows here.

226
00:13:39,072 --> 00:13:40,687
Let's push that one into the background,

227
00:13:40,687 --> 00:13:44,855
just come right on through,
and that'll push him back.

228
00:13:46,537 --> 00:13:47,950
It's scary to have this much power

229
00:13:47,950 --> 00:13:50,283
that you can move mountains.

230
00:14:00,697 --> 00:14:02,197
Okay, this, there.

231
00:14:04,384 --> 00:14:06,231
We can swing this around
and bring these two

232
00:14:06,231 --> 00:14:07,481
right together.

233
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:13,340
Just make a nice little ridge out of that.

234
00:14:15,357 --> 00:14:18,774
Okay, now we've got an almighty mountain.

235
00:14:20,227 --> 00:14:22,971
I'm gonna take a little
of the blue, brown,

236
00:14:22,971 --> 00:14:27,514
alizarin crimson, add a little
touch of sap green to it.

237
00:14:27,514 --> 00:14:31,173
Looking for a dark color here, very dark.

238
00:14:31,173 --> 00:14:33,014
I will load up this one-inch brush,

239
00:14:33,014 --> 00:14:36,296
and we'll push in some
little dark areas here.

240
00:14:36,296 --> 00:14:38,397
This'll be our little
trees that are way, way

241
00:14:38,397 --> 00:14:40,496
back in the distance, bushes and trees

242
00:14:40,495 --> 00:14:44,328
and all the little things
happening back here.

243
00:14:50,038 --> 00:14:51,038
There we go.

244
00:14:52,673 --> 00:14:54,528
Now with the big brush,
we can pull a little bit

245
00:14:54,528 --> 00:14:56,111
of this color down.

246
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,000
And this'll be the beginning
of our reflections.

247
00:15:05,504 --> 00:15:08,527
Okay, and we'll just give
it a little bit of ripple

248
00:15:08,527 --> 00:15:10,444
to make it look watery.

249
00:15:15,535 --> 00:15:17,702
(banging)

250
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:25,336
Okay, let's put some highlights on here.

251
