00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:42,702
Mm.

257
00:15:46,104 --> 00:15:48,538
There we go, all these nice little bushes

258
00:15:48,538 --> 00:15:50,011
happening back here.

259
00:15:50,011 --> 00:15:53,094
(lively piano music)

260
00:16:00,769 --> 00:16:02,072
And then we'll reflect some of that

261
00:16:02,072 --> 00:16:04,654
right down into the water here.

262
00:16:08,604 --> 00:16:09,604
There we go.

263
00:16:12,085 --> 00:16:14,495
Now with a big brush and
the most delicate, delicate

264
00:16:14,495 --> 00:16:18,063
touch possible, just
enough to pull the paint

265
00:16:18,063 --> 00:16:21,616
a little bit, we'll pull that down

266
00:16:21,616 --> 00:16:25,783
and just give it a watery
effect, don't wanna destroy it.

267
00:16:27,793 --> 00:16:29,711
Okay, now let's take...

268
00:16:33,232 --> 00:16:36,864
mix up a lot of dark here,
blue, brown, alizarin,

269
00:16:36,865 --> 00:16:39,456
and a little bit of sap green.

270
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:41,538
Should look black to you.

271
00:16:44,778 --> 00:16:48,945
And we'll load the brush
full of paint, load it full.

272
00:16:51,836 --> 00:16:53,086
A lot of paint.

273
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:56,230
And let's make some little evergreen trees

274
00:16:56,230 --> 00:16:58,509
that are growing way back
here in the distance.

275
00:16:58,509 --> 00:17:01,591
(lively piano music)

276
00:17:06,075 --> 00:17:06,908
Okay.

277
00:17:10,269 --> 00:17:13,876
Let's firm that one up a little bit.

278
00:17:13,876 --> 00:17:16,557
It needs to be a little stronger.

279
00:17:16,557 --> 00:17:17,557
There we go.

280
00:17:21,134 --> 00:17:25,969
Maybe he's got a friend
that lives right over here.

281
00:17:25,969 --> 00:17:27,134
Just dropped him in.

282
00:17:27,134 --> 00:17:30,218
(lively piano music)

283
00:17:38,646 --> 00:17:40,789
Okay, maybe they're
getting a little bigger

284
00:17:40,789 --> 00:17:43,206
as it comes around the curve.

285
00:17:54,106 --> 00:17:56,940
Maybe a little baby one back here.

286
00:18:03,070 --> 00:18:06,903
Okay, we'll put a little
bush in front of him.

287
00:18:09,468 --> 00:18:13,505
Okay, we'll take a little
touch of Magic White,

288
00:18:13,505 --> 00:18:15,338
a little bit of brown,

289
00:18:18,079 --> 00:18:19,836
and a little touch of yellow

290
00:18:19,836 --> 00:18:23,170
just to make a nice sandy looking color.

291
00:18:25,296 --> 00:18:29,212
And we'll lay in a little
water line back here.

292
00:18:35,884 --> 00:18:36,884
There we go.

293
00:18:40,214 --> 00:18:41,830
And we'll cut in a few little trunks

294
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,171
and sticks here and there.

295
00:18:44,172 --> 00:18:46,422
(scraping)

296
00:18:56,605 --> 00:18:57,438
Okay.

297
00:19:02,509 --> 00:19:06,403
Maybe we need another tree right here.

298
00:19:06,403 --> 00:19:07,434
Trees are getting closer,

299
00:19:07,434 --> 00:19:09,288
so they're getting a little bigger.

300
00:19:09,288 --> 00:19:10,813
They look bigger to you, this is the way

301
00:19:10,813 --> 00:19:13,479
we push everything back.

302
00:19:13,479 --> 00:19:15,729
Work with perspective here.

303
00:19:23,469 --> 00:19:25,999
Okay, let's move to the
other side of the picture

304
00:19:25,999 --> 00:19:28,788
while we've got a brush
full of paint here,

305
00:19:28,788 --> 00:19:32,288
and we'll put an almighty tree right here.

306
00:19:37,017 --> 00:19:38,158
These trees live in your brush.

307
00:19:38,157 --> 00:19:42,397
You have to scare 'em out
sometimes, really work at 'em.

308
00:19:42,397 --> 00:19:45,980
Little son of a guns
will try to avoid you.

309
00:19:49,817 --> 00:19:50,920
And they're like everything else.

310
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,773
The first time you try 'em, they're gonna

311
00:19:52,772 --> 00:19:54,627
drive you up the wall.

312
00:19:54,627 --> 00:19:56,633
But you practice it.

313
00:19:56,633 --> 00:20:00,145
If there's a secret to
this, it is practice.

314
00:20:00,145 --> 00:20:03,263
You learn how to make the brush work,

315
00:20:03,263 --> 00:20:05,505
how to touch the canvas with it.

316
00:20:05,506 --> 00:20:09,006
And then it's just a matter of practicing.

317
00:20:11,105 --> 00:20:13,162
First time you tied your
shoe, it wasn't easy.

318
00:20:13,162 --> 00:20:15,598
You had to look at it and work at it.

319
00:20:15,598 --> 00:20:17,016
The next thing you know, you're not paying

320
00:20:17,017 --> 00:20:19,912
any attention, you just,
you get your shoe tied.

321
00:20:19,912 --> 00:20:20,828
Same thing.

322
00:20:25,204 --> 00:20:26,788
Okay, we'll just...

323
00:20:29,744 --> 00:20:31,150
Maybe we'll make another little projection

324
00:20:31,151 --> 00:20:35,259
come right out through here, there we go.

325
00:20:35,259 --> 00:20:37,592
A little reflection in here.

326
00:20:40,132 --> 00:20:41,548
And we'll pull that down.

327
00:20:41,548 --> 00:20:44,632
(lively piano music)

328
00:20:51,839 --> 00:20:54,023
Okay, we'll lay in some more of these

329
00:20:54,023 --> 00:20:56,657
pretty colors back here.

330
00:20:56,657 --> 00:20:59,907
There's a nice little bush right there.

331
00:21:04,026 --> 00:21:05,359
Mm, there's one.

332
00:21:09,233 --> 00:21:13,233
And right down here we'll
reflect some of these.

333
00:21:21,868 --> 00:21:25,084
Okay, delicate touch
again, very, very light.

334
00:21:25,085 --> 00:21:29,251
Just enough to move it a
little bit on the wet canvas.

335
00:21:32,339 --> 00:21:33,568
And we'll put some land out here

336
00:21:33,568 --> 00:21:36,568
so these bushes have a place to sit.

337
00:21:38,446 --> 00:21:41,661
Don't want 'em fall off in the river here,

338
00:21:41,662 --> 00:21:45,245
so we'll give 'em
something to set on here.

339
00:21:46,789 --> 00:21:50,009
And we can take a clean brush
and just lift that gently.

340
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:53,517
This is a very thin paint
now, it's mostly Magic White.

341
00:21:53,517 --> 00:21:55,025
So you can move that without destroying

342
00:21:55,025 --> 00:21:56,775
what's underneath it.

343
00:21:58,836 --> 00:22:01,565
And here we'll use a little bit of just

344
00:22:01,565 --> 00:22:03,315
straight Magic White,

345
00:22:04,339 --> 00:22:08,506
and we'll put us a happy
little water line in here.

346
00:22:11,459 --> 00:22:12,292
There.

347
00:22:17,172 --> 00:22:18,005
Okay.

348
00:22:20,432 --> 00:22:23,765
Now then, you can, you can put some more

349
00:22:25,991 --> 00:22:28,991
little bushes right in here like so.

350
00:22:32,478 --> 00:22:36,394
And we'll drop some
reflections into the water.

351
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,291
And we'll pull those down.

352
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:48,215
And anybody can do this, this
is not some big secret thing.

353
00:22:48,215 --> 00:22:51,395
Anybody can do it, we teach
people from the age of 10

354
00:22:51,395 --> 00:22:54,807
all the way up 80 and 90 years old.

355
00:22:54,807 --> 00:22:56,974
(banging)

356
00:23:00,363 --> 00:23:04,072
And young people really, really like this.

357
00:23:04,071 --> 00:23:07,382
They learn it very easily, very quickly,

358
00:23:07,383 --> 00:23:10,216
and they see results very quickly.

359
00:23:11,236 --> 00:23:14,985
I have a son that's a young man right now,

360
00:23:14,984 --> 00:23:16,836
and he was, oh, he's been painting

361
00:23:16,836 --> 00:23:21,002
since he was about 12 years
old, been selling his work.

362
00:23:24,304 --> 00:23:27,565
So it's not just for the older person.

363
00:23:27,565 --> 00:23:32,400
It will also work very
well for the young person.

364
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:35,262
The only trouble, like
my son, he's quite lazy.

365
00:23:35,261 --> 00:23:37,327
He'll only paint if he needs money.

366
00:23:37,327 --> 00:23:40,598
If he needs money, he'll paint.

367
00:23:40,598 --> 00:23:44,765
But it is a nice way to put
a happy buck in your pocket.

368
00:23:45,660 --> 00:23:49,410
And to make good things
happen in your heart.

369
00:23:50,438 --> 00:23:54,864
Okay, we'll just have this come
right on down through here.

370
00:23:54,864 --> 00:23:55,947
Fill that in.

371
00:24:03,398 --> 00:24:06,716
Okay, now we can start
highlighting some of these things.

372
00:24:06,717 --> 00:24:10,773
We'll take a little bit of
blue and yellow mixed together,

373
00:24:10,772 --> 00:24:14,727
make a very nice little green color here.

374
00:24:14,728 --> 00:24:17,361
And we'll just drop some
highlights on this tree.

375
00:24:17,361 --> 00:24:18,864
Remember where your light's coming from.

376
00:24:18,864 --> 00:24:21,459
Light's coming from the right,

377
00:24:21,459 --> 00:24:23,024
so you want the right-hand
side of this tree

378
00:24:23,023 --> 00:24:27,190
to be a little more distinct
and bright than the left side.

379
00:24:28,281 --> 00:24:29,688
And if you're right handed,
you'll probably find

380
00:24:29,689 --> 00:24:33,548
it's easier to have the
light coming from the right.

381
00:24:33,548 --> 00:24:35,250
If you're left handed,
it will sort of vary

382
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:37,083
from person to person.

383
00:24:38,641 --> 00:24:39,474
Okay.

384
00:24:42,574 --> 00:24:44,250
Let's put some little highlights over here

385
00:24:44,250 --> 00:24:46,084
on these little trees.

386
00:24:47,356 --> 00:24:49,773
The sun wouldn't forget them.

387
00:24:50,775 --> 00:24:51,793
There we go.

388
00:24:51,792 --> 00:24:54,875
(lively piano music)

389
00:25:00,125 --> 00:25:01,541
There we are now.

390
00:25:03,285 --> 00:25:08,277
A little more Magic White,
thin that down just a touch.

391
00:25:08,277 --> 00:25:10,955
And we can start finding all
these beautiful little trees

392
00:25:10,954 --> 00:25:14,602
and bushes that are living in here.

393
00:25:14,603 --> 00:25:17,247
Very important that you don't
kill all this dark area.

394
00:25:17,247 --> 00:25:18,101
If you kill all the dark,

395
00:25:18,101 --> 00:25:20,934
your picture's gonna be very flat.

396
00:25:22,683 --> 00:25:23,953
Well, we might as well reflect that

397
00:25:23,953 --> 00:25:26,203
right into the water there.

398
00:25:27,763 --> 00:25:29,596
Okay, and there we go.

399
00:25:30,784 --> 00:25:33,034
A little bit right in here.

400
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,766
And we'll reflect that right on down,

401
00:25:35,766 --> 00:25:38,682
a little touch of red over the top.

402
00:25:41,286 --> 00:25:44,452
Okay, there's another nice tree I see.

403
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:48,339
Little rascals live in your brush,

404
00:25:48,339 --> 00:25:50,673
you just gotta push 'em out.

405
00:25:54,390 --> 00:25:58,140
And let's put a touch
more of the Magic here.

406
00:25:59,358 --> 00:26:01,358
There, nice ochre color.

407
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:12,175
All these pretty little bushes,

408
00:26:12,175 --> 00:26:14,925
just let 'em flow off your brush.

409
00:26:20,905 --> 00:26:25,883
And some little grassy areas
coming down through here.

410
00:26:25,883 --> 00:26:29,133
Let's turn that into a nice reflection.

411
00:26:29,982 --> 00:26:31,066
Just like so.

412
00:26:33,484 --> 00:26:37,317
Okay, now let's give him
a little bit of dirt.

413
00:26:40,271 --> 00:26:41,271
There we go.

414
00:26:43,150 --> 00:26:45,831
This is straight van dyke brown.

415
00:26:45,830 --> 00:26:50,311
And onto that, we'll take
a little brown and white

416
00:26:50,311 --> 00:26:52,455
and give him just a
little touch of highlight,

417
00:26:52,455 --> 00:26:54,308
make him look like little stones and rocks

418
00:26:54,308 --> 00:26:56,058
playing through here.

419
00:26:58,951 --> 00:27:03,378
Okay, let's put a few little
sticks here and there.

420
00:27:03,378 --> 00:27:04,897
Here we're just cutting through the paint

421
00:27:04,897 --> 00:27:08,072
using the point of the knife.

422
00:27:08,073 --> 00:27:12,240
But it shows distance, it shows
all these different planes.

423
00:27:15,759 --> 00:27:16,592
Okay.

424
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,220
And we'll put just a little
bit of Magic White under here

425
00:27:20,220 --> 00:27:21,999
and give us a little water line.

